**Abstract:**
Working notes dated July 9, 1992 outlining a philosophical project to show structural similarity between ethics and theology regarding the inseparability of knowledge from desire. The document questions whether theology, like ethics, should follow phronesis rather than episteme as its model. Engages with Nussbaum's Fragility of Goodness on Aristotle's treatment of emotions and the "science of the good."

**AI Recommendation:** Important methodological notes connecting to the larger faith-reason research project.

